      "content": "i mean, if the \"consensus\" is that it's fundamentally broken, doesn't that kind of delegitimize any of the good it actually does? like, some might say that calling it \"fundamentally flawed\" treats the idea of international cooperation itself as a failed experiment, whereas others would say it's just a tool that's only as good as the countries using it. isn't that a bit of a biased way to frame it?",
